        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-08-30T15:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-08-30T15:14:00-05:00" n="205"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <head>205. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Republic of China</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d205fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 711.56393/5–456. Top Secret. Drafted in <gloss target="#t_CA1"
                            >CA</gloss> by <persName>Douglas N. Forman</persName>, cleared in <gloss
                            target="#t_CA1">CA</gloss> by <persName corresp="#p_CRN1"
                            >Clough</persName> and in <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> by <persName
                            corresp="#p_SWJ1">Sebald</persName>, and approved by <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWS1">Robertson</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-08-30T16:14:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 30, 1956—4:14 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>170. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 978.<note n="2" xml:id="d205fn2">
                        <ref target="#d173">Document 173</ref>.</note> Inform Chinese Government
                    U.S. desires position flight of Matador missiles on Taiwan. Missiles will make
                    distinct contribution toward improving defensibility Taiwan and U.S. hopes
                        <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> willing cooperate this project. If
                        <gloss target="#t_GRC1">GRC</gloss> agrees in principle, we will make
                    detailed proposal at early date.<note n="3" xml:id="d205fn3">In telegram 209
                        from Taipei, September 2, the Embassy reported that the Foreign Ministry
                        agreed and welcomed the proposal to position a flight of Matador missiles on
                        Taiwan. (Department of State, Central Files, 711.56393/9–256)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
